- Firmware update failure.
- Extended filesystem unavailability.
- Update interruption due to an existing disk rebuild or hardware issue.
- Backup or restore job failure if activity is not stopped before the change.

Mitigation:
The activity will be performed during an approved maintenance window, after confirming system health and stopping all backup, restore and replication activity. The Dell documented procedure will be followed.
